WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Running LLMs is not just deploying a model. It is a platform engineering problem.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:18.000
LLM platforms must control latency, GPU placement, cost, security, and rollback.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:32.000
A production cluster separates system services, app workloads, and GPU inference capacity.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:48.000
The inference stack separates gateway behavior, autoscaling, model runtime, GPU capacity, and telemetry.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:01:00.000
KServe is strong for standardized platform APIs. Ray Serve is strong for programmable serving graphs.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:18.000
Production RAG has two lifecycles: ingestion quality and online serving latency.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:30.000
GitOps makes change reviewable. Observability makes production behavior visible.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:40.000
Design the platform before scaling the model.
